<section id="menus.goto">
  <title>Go To</title>

  <note><para>This menu displays entries only when a project is open.</para>
  <para>Key shortcut description reminder: <link linkend="appendix.shortcut" endterm="shortcut_description"/></para>
    <example><title>Next Untranslated Segment</title>
  		<para>In this manual:
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>u</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
		<para>On Windows and Linux:
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>Control</keycap><keycap>U</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
		<para>On macOS:
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>Command</keycap><keycap>U</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
		</example>
</note>

  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry id="menus.goto.next.untranslated.segment">
      <term id="menus.goto.next.untranslated.segment.title">Next Untranslated Segment</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Moves to the next segment that has no equivalent in the
        translation memory.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>u</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry id="menus.goto.next.translated.segment">
      <term id="menus.goto.next.translated.segment.title">Next Translated Segment</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Moves to the next already translated segment, ignoring
        untranslated segments.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>u</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry id="menus.goto.next.segment">
      <term id="menus.goto.next.segment.title">Next Segment</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Moves to the next segment. If the current segment is the last
        segment in a file, it moves to the first segment of the next
        file.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>n</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>Enter</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>

        <note><para><keycap>TAB</keycap> replaces <keycap>Enter</keycap> as an
        alternate shortcut if <link
        linkend="dialogs.preferences.general.use.tab.to.advance">Use TAB to
        Advance</link> option is selected.</para>
		<para>This is useful for character entry systems that use
		<keycap>Enter</keycap> to validate input.</para></note>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Previous Segment</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Moves to the previous segment. If the current segment is the
        first one in a file, it moves to the last segment of the previous
        file.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>p</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>Enter</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>

        <note><para><keycombo><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>TAB</keycap></keycombo>
        replaces <keycombo><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>Enter</keycap></keycombo>
        as an alternate shortcut if <link
        linkend="dialogs.preferences.general.use.tab.to.advance">Use TAB to
        Advance</link> option is selected.</para>
		<para>This is useful for character entry systems that use
		<keycap>Enter</keycap> to validate input.</para></note>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Segment number...</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>The segment is opened when either its segment call-out or
        segment number is entered.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>j</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Next Note</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>The next segment with a note attached to it, will open.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Previous Note</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>The previous segment with a note will open.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Next Unique Segment</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Moves to the next unique segment.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>q</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>

      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Source of Selected Match</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Moves to the segment that does correspond to the current
        selected match in the <guilabel>Fuzzy matches</guilabel> pane.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>m</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>

      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Forward in history...</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>OmegaT remembers the segments your segment navigation
        history.</para>
		<para>With this command you can move forward one segment at a time to
		the segments that you have previously visited with <link
		linkend="menu.goto.backinhistory"
		endterm="menu.goto.backinhistory"/>.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>n</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term id="menu.goto.backinhistory">Back in history...</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>OmegaT remembers the segments your segment navigation
        history.</para>
        <para>With this command you can move backward one segment at a time to
        the segments that your have previously visited.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>p</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</section>
